<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910823-0017</DOCNO><DOCID>910823-0017.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Robertson-Ceco Corp.:   Charge Related to Lawsuit   To Be Taken in 3rd Period</HL><DATE>08/23/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11</SO><CO>   RHH</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Robertson-Ceco Corp. said it will take a $4.3 millionthird-quarter charge for discontinued operations related tosettlement of a lawsuit.   The Pittsburgh-based manufacturing and constructionconcern said it received $3 million cash as a result of thesettlement. The suit against the company related to acurtainwall project that was discontinued in 1988. Thecompany, in a counterclaim to the suit, was seeking a $7.3million payment representing the amount due on the contract.Robertson-Ceco doesn't have comparable year-ago figuresbecause it was created by a merger in November 1990.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>